3.text: Once there lived a little Red Hen. She lived with her chickens. She lived in a farm. There were also a Goose and a Duck in the farm. One day, she found a grain of wheat.

4.text: “I am going to plant the wheat. Who will help me?” she asked.

5.text: “Not I. I am busy,” said the Goose.

6.text: “Not I. I am busy,” said the Duck.

7.text: “I will plant, then,” said the little Red Hen, and she planted the grain of wheat.

8.text: She watered it, and it grew well. Later, she got a good harvest of wheat. “I am taking the wheat to the mill. Who will help me?” she asked.

9.text: “Not I. I am busy,” said the Goose.

10.text: “Not I. I am busy,” said the Duck.

11.text: “I will take it myself, then,” said the little Red Hen, and she took the wheat to the mill.

12.text: Then she brought back the flour. “I am going to make some bread. Who will help me?” she asked.

13.text: “Not I. I am busy,” said the Goose.

14.text: “Not I. I am busy,” said the Duck.

15.text: “I will make it myself, then,” said the little Red Hen.
